oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Armed Forces Day Parade, Nashville, Tennessee, 1951 May 19
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: A photo related to the Armed Forces Day Parade held in Nashville, Tennessee on May 19th, 1951. Governor Gordon Browning and Gen. Clifton B. Cates reviewed troops from the podium at the War Memorial Buildings at the commemoration in downtown Nashville, Tennessee. Gen. Clifton B. Cates, Marine Corps commandant (1948-52) was born in Tiptonville, Tennessee. Forms part of Record Group 3, Metro Davidson County Photographer. 1 photograph negative : b & w ; 4 x 5 in.
